KwaZulu-Natal emergency workers have threatened to shutdown paramedic and mortuary services during the busy Easter period, if their demands are not met.

A handful of these workers marched to the ANC provincial offices on Monday, demanding the party intervene. They want the ANC to hold health MEC Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo accountable for “contraventions” of labour court judgements in their favour over salaries and special payments.





“We have engaged with comrade (Premier Willis) Mchunu and comrade Dhlomo to no prevail, further we have followed all labour forum but the officials and comrade Dhlomo are refusing to implement court decisions and DPSA (Department of Public Service and Administration) instructions. Instead, they threaten us with dismissal. Already, others are dismissed thus leaving us with no choice but to approach the organisation (ANC),” read the memorandum.













