Verbal blows exchanged between ANC KZN's Super Zuma and ex paramedic Sfiso Zuma over deadline for response to memorandum. 
Video: Nosipho Mngoma



The marchers were led by axed paramedic Sfiso Dlamini who got into verbal blows with ANC representative Super Zuma, over the marchers demand that the ANC respond within seven days. If this is not done, they will “camp” outside the ANC provincial offices during Easter, leaving the province without "anyone to pick up bodies or treat and transport the sick and injured."

Zuma  said they could not agree to the deadline as there was no telling how long the process would take. “We will process the memorandum and take it to the relevant structure. If there are people who need to account, we will call them to account. I hear you on the seven days, but we work on the process and not within a time frame,” he said.

 KZN EMS /paramedics outside @MYANC provincial headquarters calling for them to recall MEC Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo. @TheMercurySA pic.twitter.com/55GHE8FRQT
